#: ../../L/line-eater--the.rst:11
msgid ""
"[Usenet] A bug in some now-obsolete versions of the netnews software that "
"used to eat up to BUFSIZ bytes of the article text. The bug was triggered by"
" having the text of the article start with a space or tab. This bug was "
"quickly personified as a mythical creature called the line eater, and "
"postings often included a dummy line of line eater food. Ironically, line "
"eater ‘food’ not beginning with a space or tab wasn't actually eaten, since "
"the bug was avoided; but if there *was* a space or tab before it, then the "
"line eater would eat the food *and* the beginning of the text it was "
"supposed to be protecting. The practice of sacrificing to the line eater "
"continued for some time after the bug had been :ref:`nailed-to-the-wall`\\, "
"and is still humorously referred to. The bug itself was still occasionally "
"reported to be lurking in some mail-to-netnews gateways as late as 1991."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet] "
"今では廃れたnetnewsソフトの一部の版にあったバグで、記事テキストを最大BUFSIZバイトまで食ってしまうもの。このバグは、記事のテキストがスペースやタブで始まると発動した。このバグはまもなくline"
" eaterと呼ばれる神話上の生き物として擬人化され、投稿にはしばしばダミーの一行のline "
"eaterのえさが含まれた。皮肉なことに、スペースやタブで始まらないline "
"eaterの‘えさ’は、バグが回避されるので実際には食べられなかった。しかしその前にスペースやタブが\\ *あった*\\ 場合、line "
"eaterはえさを食べ、\\ *さらに*\\ 守るはずだったテキストの冒頭をも食べてしまった。line eaterに生贄を捧げる慣習は、このバグが\\ "
":ref:`nailed-to-the-wall`\\ "
"にされた後もしばらく続き、今でもユーモアをこめて言及される。バグそのものは、1991年になっても一部のメール-"
"netnewsゲートウェイに潜んでいるとときどき報告された。"

